{
  "buggy_files": [
    "net/sunrpc/socklib.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "xdr_partial_copy_from_skb"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "In xdr_partial_copy_from_skb() at lines 96-101, when there is a page_base offset, the pglen (page length to copy) is decremented by the original base value BEFORE base is adjusted by adding xdr->page_base and masking. This causes an incorrect pglen value to be used in the subsequent page copying loop, leading to buffer overrun/underrun when copying RPC reply data. Specifically, on line 97, 'pglen -= base' should occur AFTER lines 98-100 which adjust base to represent the actual offset within the first page. The correct order should be: (1) add page_base to base, (2) calculate ppage offset, (3) mask base to get in-page offset, (4) THEN subtract the adjusted base from pglen. This bug causes RPC reply buffers to be incompletely or incorrectly copied, resulting in XDR decoding failures that manifest as 'getattr failed' errors in NFS inode revalidation, which is particularly problematic during autofs mount expiration when inode revalidation is triggered."
}

